Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.27,0:00:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll resume. Can you all hear me? We'll resume and I'm going to sign books and as I sign books\Npeople will ask questions and I'll answer them, not as complexly as we did before.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.85,0:00:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We just calibrated the level of aesthetics because in a way aesthetics are part of the\Npartial answer to some of the questions. Aesthetics becomes a prominent part of the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.57,0:01:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,human psyche around calibrated level 360. Just beyond Chinese fortune cookies.\NAesthetics. So you know many could give many answers to the questions
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.76,0:01:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but one of the appreciations of life is the awareness of beauty and the part that it plays\Nin your decision making and your values of life. You know we saw a dog during the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.96,0:01:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,lunch break, stunningly beautiful, this black stunning dog. Not only its lovingness\Nbut its stunning beauty you know and so you begin to appreciate the beauty of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.45,0:01:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If you blindfold somebody and take their blindfold off I can tell you the consciousness\Nlevel of where I am by looking about two feet around me because when you're in certain dangerous
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.21,0:02:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,parts of the world they all look the same. There's litter, there's trash, there's\Ngraffiti, there's a complete lack of appreciation for beauty and when you see the emergence
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.59,0:02:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of respect for beauty then salvation is not far. So in answer to a question that came\Nup this morning, what can we do for the children individually and collectively? I think teaching
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.06,0:02:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,them the appreciation of aesthetics. If I look back at my own childhood what the visual\Ndo I value most? Well, Midwest lifestyle of the 30s, etc., had a certain profound inner
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.09,0:02:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,value of itself. But the things that accrued to that was an intense appreciation for beauty\Nin all of its forms. So the fortunate part of my own lifetime was my parents were musical,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.46,0:03:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,my father was a musician. We were all very sensitive to aesthetics and traditional religion.\NTo be in a great cathedral, there I am a boy soprano singing Pontus Angelicus with a full
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.62,0:03:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,orchestra in a full cathedral, with the stained glass windows and a full choir and a full\Naudience hanging on every obbligato-soprano note. It was ethereal. It was like unreal
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.30,0:03:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and it imprinted.\NIt imprints beauty. So one of the expressions of divinity is aesthetics and beauty. And
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.50,0:03:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the answer to the gentleman's question, what can we do for the children that are under\Nsuch assault by that which is non-integrative in our society, is to expose them to real
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.75,0:04:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,beauty and aesthetics. The appreciation for opera. As a boy, I listened on Saturday afternoon\NMilton Krauss from the Metropolitan Opera.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.68,0:04:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, I knew all about the Nibelungen Ring and the Wagner and the Bizet, all those\Nthings just as a boy, as a boy. So if I had to do it over again, I would express as much
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.43,0:04:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,energy as I can in directing the children in aesthetics. Ballet dancing, there's nothing\Nmore exquisite than seeing a pas de deux from a great ballet, you know. And we have tickets
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.54,0:04:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,for it this year.\NThe only time I rode to Phoenix to see La Boheme, you know, in the spring, or a great
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.69,0:04:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,ballet, the Sadler-Wells Ballet. So in a small town, in Wisconsin, which I'm sure from the\Nviewpoint of LA or New York is the sticks, we never missed a thing, you see, because
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.66,0:04:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,we didn't take it for granted. So when the Sadler-Wells Ballet came through or when,\Nyou know, Paderewski came through or Gala Kirche or somebody great came through, we
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.54,0:05:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,went.\NSo that was great.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.63,0:05:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So the answer then I wanted to give was aesthetics would be the counterbalance to ugliness. So\Nthe dominion of ugliness is negated by the inner appreciation of beauty, because once
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.33,0:05:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you have an inner appreciation of beauty, ugliness stands forth as ugliness. And it\Nmay be stylish, it may be hip, it may be cool, but the fact that it's ugly is quite obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.93,0:05:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Teaching our children aesthetics and communicating…\NYou know…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.74,0:05:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,…and communicating our appreciation and love and value of aesthetics, I think is probably\Nthe best counter for us, a counterbalance we can give to ugliness and the danger of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.30,0:05:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,ugliness to the psyche of the children. I know you didn't ask me, but I know you'd\Nlike that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.19,0:06:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's proceed, yeah?\NAnd I can say, you know, my obligation to you is to be that which I am to the greatest
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.44,0:06:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,extent as I can be to a greater extent.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.64,0:06:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to you, to be radically all that I can be, and thus serve you is my joy.\NAnd I would like to thank you personally, and this is a token of my appreciation of all the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.73,0:06:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,good things you've done for me this year and for everyone else. This is the latest Robert Gass CD.\NThis is the music we listen to, Kyrie and Alleluia. Yes, he's wonderful. This is his
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.64,0:06:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,latest and greatest, and I'd like to offer it to you as a Christmas offering. Thank you so much.\NThank you so much. Yes. First, thank you very much again. I have not been very comfortable with
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.62,0:07:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the calibration or the kinesiological process. I was hoping that you might do two calibrations\Nfor me if you'd have a problem. No. You'd have a problem. All right. There's a spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.76,0:07:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,teacher in India by the name of Gurinder Singh, and I'm curious where he\Ncalibrates. I'm curious where he calibrates. I'm curious where he calibrates. I'm curious where
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.08,0:07:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,his teachings calibrate at. I can't really do that right now. You know, we prepared quite a huge\Nvolume about it. To answer these things correctly, they have to be contextualized in a certain way
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.04,0:07:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,so as to avoid judgmentalism. See? Otherwise, you think 440 is better than 420. I understand.\NNot necessarily so, because the task of 440 is different than the task of 220.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.37,0:07:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not better than. Each level of consciousness addresses its own level.\NSo, a person at 420 can be an excellent teacher at 420, and somebody at 480 can be a very bad teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.06,0:08:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see, the excellence is on its own level. So, I can say, well, Einstein only reached 499.\NOn the other hand, 499, the Einstein level that he reached, you know, has changed the whole world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.26,0:08:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it isn't just a calibrated level of consciousness, but the whole contextualization of it and the\Ntiming of it. See?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.50,0:08:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess what my intent is, it's not so much to place a judgment on where he is as much as a protection\Nthat I'm not with the charlatan one way or the other. And, I mean, I don't feel that at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.64,0:08:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh.\NSo, more my curiosity is...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.82,0:08:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why are you asking?\NWell, it's been 20 years, and I haven't, you know, there's four requirements.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.38,0:08:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The fourth one being initiation, which he gives you a mantra.\NIt's been 20 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.88,0:08:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I've danced around him.\NI have not made that plunge.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.30,0:08:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh.\NI see what you're asking.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.35,0:08:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll ask you in a different way later and not in full.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.35,0:08:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,See, what you really want to know is the appropriateness of where you're at is really the question you're asking, right?\NWell, by that you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.37,0:09:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the reason you're asking me the question?\NIt's the appropriateness of where you're at and the step you want to take.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.19,0:09:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.\NYou're not asking me about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.00,0:09:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You're asking me about yourself.\NThat's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.66,0:09:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThat's a different question.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.38,0:09:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.37,0:09:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll answer you afterwards.\NFantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.50,0:09:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYou know, is a certain move appropriate for where you're at at a given time is really the question you're asking, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.33,0:09:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIt's got nothing to do with him, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.78,0:09:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Fantastic.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.47,0:09:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Because at the wrong time, Jesus is the wrong person to worship, understand?\NBecause you'd be seeing him in a way that would not be helpful.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.99,0:09:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.15,0:09:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NI don't have a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.39,0:09:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if you can send these books.\NI just really enjoy being in your presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.36,0:10:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I feel that my mind is quiet when I'm close to you.\NCan I give you a hug?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.66,0:10:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, he's got a lot of muscles.\NLook out when you scream.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.89,0:10:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy's a mesomorph.\NI once had a buddy, and he'd had a couple of beers, and he dropped in to visit me, and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.20,0:10:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,he gave me a big hug and broke three of them on one side.\NI didn't tell him, because I knew it would hurt his feelings, and he'd feel guilty about
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.74,0:10:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\NSo I just kept it to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.74,0:10:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But I tell him, go, crump, crump, crump.\NThey healed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.24,0:10:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a tough winter, though.\NTo celebrate, I went country riding.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.24,0:10:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to a lot of places.\NI went to a lot of places.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.57,0:10:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to a lot of places.\NI went to a lot of places.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.87,0:10:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to Western dancing, and I turned this girl who's called a dip, I think, to go underneath\Nmy arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.50,0:10:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,She ducked under her arm, or she missed, and her head hit me, my ribs on the other side,\Nand broke them on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.90,0:11:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It was busted rib winter.\NFirst three on one side, then three on the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.69,0:11:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So I went to see an orthopedist.\NI said, what is this with the busted ribs all the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.84,0:11:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, you need more calcium.\NSo I've been taking calcium ever since, and I haven't broken a rib since.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.39,0:11:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm careful who I hug, that's all.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.65,0:11:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What's happening when you have a spontaneous movement out of form, and then you get pulled\Nback?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.09,0:11:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Years go by, maybe it happens, I guess, two, three times versus working at this and getting\Nto it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.49,0:11:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, because that's the way it usually comes on.\NIt's like feelings, like you'll suddenly out of nowhere have a presence of light within
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.98,0:12:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself, and it illuminates all things, and you're beyond all time.\NIt's stunning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.89,0:12:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's stunning, and it's very distinct.\NAnd then the next day, it's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.72,0:12:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, well, where'd it go?\NSo that's the great night of the soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.24,0:12:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Lord, where hast thou gone?\NWhat have I done wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.84,0:12:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,How come thou hast deserted me?\NThe Christian saints, you know, the bridegroom, what have you left me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.04,0:12:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NThose are the wings of the soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.97,0:12:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And they soar.\NAnd what you see is your own destiny ahead, that's your destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.16,0:12:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So you just go back to doing what you're doing and working your spiritual program to the\Nbest of your ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.27,0:12:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it becomes more and more predominant, but it may come very intensely and leave a\Nnumber of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.28,0:12:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it first came on to me at age three, then it came on again at age 12 in the snowbank.\NThen it came recurrently.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.27,0:13:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And it would leave for five or six years, you know.\NAnd I learned, do not pine for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.54,0:13:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Just do whatever you're doing with the same devotion and stop looking for dessert.\NSo I say, oh, Lord, let me surrender my appetite for that delicious dessert and serve you during
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.78,0:13:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the ordinary meal of everyday life, see?\NBecause in that state, you can't function anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.33,0:13:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You're useless as a human being.\NYou sit there smiling sweetly at everybody, embracing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.05,0:13:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray for peace.\NSo it could be that you've got something else of equal importance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.67,0:13:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only to tell you that, yes, you are on the pathway, and it gives you like a preliminary\Nassurance of the reality of that level of reality, that even if you experience it for
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.17,0:13:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,seconds, you now know it, and it leaves an imprint in your consciousness that will never\Nleave.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.67,0:14:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah, it leaves a vibrational frequency in your aura, and it doesn't ever forget it.\NNever forgets it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.53,0:14:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll never be satisfied with anything less.\NThanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.13,0:14:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?\NCould you elaborate on the psychic attacks that you endured and how you endured them?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.98,0:14:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Psychic attacks were something I didn't believe in.\NIt sounded very New Age-y and yah, yah, yah, baloney stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.65,0:14:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was only when they became...\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.03,0:14:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NIt was only when they became severe, then I used the diagnostic consciousness techniques
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.86,0:15:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to discern what it is, and also through prayer, how to undo it, what the error is.\NBeyond a certain level, consciousness is like you're not allowed to hang on to an error.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.00,0:15:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like your commitment has already demanded that you let go of that error.\NLet go of that error.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.59,0:15:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Let go of that error.\NI found that anguishing, it didn't happen up to a certain level.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.05,0:15:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,A certain level was exquisite bliss.\NEverything was miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.84,0:15:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything was love and exquisite beauty and oneness.\NAnd then beyond that, I forget what started the movement beyond that, but then started
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.09,0:15:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the feeling of...\NIt's like that which you have become is viewed as competitively dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.15,0:15:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.40,0:16:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,dangerous for the dominion over mankind. When you start unveiling the lies and\Nyou start taking the sheep's clothing off the wolf, you start to get bitten. And
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.00,0:16:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I was distressed by it. I found how to transcend it to find out what\Nchakra in which archetype was out about what. And through prayer and forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.38,0:16:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and asking God to see it differently, then I would feel that pain leave me. But\Nit was like your whole body was on fire with a sub-lethal level of electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.58,0:16:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Like it wasn't enough to kill you. They slowly fried you. So we were in Korea\Nwhen Susan found the answer. She pulled out. I said, God, what is this? What is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.62,0:16:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,this? What is this? And she reached in the drawer, pulled out the equivalent of the\NChristian Bible, a book of verses, and she ripped it out of the drawer. And Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.97,0:17:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddhist Bible, and she opened the page, and it says, the Buddha said that he, on his way\Nto enlightenment, he was wracked with pain and attacked by the demons, and attacked by
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.66,0:17:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the demons and wracked with pain, like his bones were broken.\NInstantly, I felt better.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.46,0:17:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, that's what's going on.\NThat's what is going, or what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.54,0:17:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what's going on.\NSo, now, instead of feeling bad about it, you say, well, you've chosen this, and now,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.90,0:17:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you see, the human nervous system isn't made for that kind of consciousness level.\NThe human nervous system is comfortable up to about 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.90,0:17:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond that, it's not, the human nervous system is not made to handle those frequencies and\Nthose high energies.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.09,0:17:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the nervous system, in this case, the nervous system had to actually become\Nheavier by accretion of proteins and various other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.55,0:17:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The nervous system literally had to adapt to the taxation of that energy frequency.\NThat's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.27,0:17:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NIt's finished doing that now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.38,0:18:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NIt's finished doing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.00,0:18:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's finished doing that.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.25,0:18:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's finished doing that.\NSo, putting 220 volts through 110 wiring system, I guess, is the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.85,0:18:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, it's adapted.\NI have permission to ask this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.35,0:18:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It has now adapted to that requirement.\NOh, that's first of God, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.07,0:18:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's relief.\NBut hearing that from the Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.18,0:18:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, sharing our spiritual experience with each other, see how meaningful it is to all of us.\NFor all of us to hear of others' experiences, you know, we all benefit to know that that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.00,0:18:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced glimpse of what's coming up spiritually in the future for you can come and go.\NWhen it happens to you and it goes, you say, well, I've heard of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.19,0:18:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you're getting it.\NIt comes and then it goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.97,0:18:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And not to feel bad.\NNot to feel bad about it, that you've done something wrong, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.83,0:19:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Just to hear of it, see.\NBecause the minute she read from the book, I felt instantly better, see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.05,0:19:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's not something commonly spoken of in our society, you know.\NI was a psychiatrist 50 years and I never heard of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.20,0:19:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I read all the great intellects of all time and I never heard of it.\NSo, hear an obscure Bible in a drawer in a hotel in South Korea.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.16,0:19:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There was the answer, you know.\NWaiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.45,0:19:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Waiting for you.\NSo, you say, dear God, you know, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.08,0:19:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,God leads your wife to open the drawer and she pulls it out and she says, here's what\Nthe Buddha said.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.33,0:19:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That was very nice of the Buddha to leave the message for us.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.18,0:19:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.90,0:19:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.51,0:19:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a question.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.70,0:20:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And what it has to do with, I guess, is when you spoke about, or when you speak about enforcing\Nor enforced.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.79,0:20:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You spoke.\NWhen you were talking about sobriety earlier, enforced sobriety.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.59,0:20:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, enforced, yes.\NAre you, are you, is that, are you speaking the same way as when you speak of force?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.25,0:20:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.70,0:20:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, karmic, you know, what's traditionally called good karma, only comes about as a\Nresult of your own personal choice, not because you're coerced to some move by somebody else.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.98,0:20:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Although, in the beginning, you could be coerced by somebody else.\NAnd later, of volition, by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.75,0:20:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That happens to people in prison.\NThey're put in prison, and there they go through a transformation of consciousness, and some
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.53,0:20:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,reach almost sainthood.\NBut that was out of the choice of free will.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.65,0:20:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In the beginning, it wasn't their free will.\NSame as some people who get sent to 12-step groups, say, A, by the judge, and they've
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.76,0:21:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,got to have other people sign that they attended.\NSo in the beginning, it may be with resentment, and then much to their own surprise, suddenly
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.89,0:21:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,they become an enthusiast.\NNow they're a genuine member.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.89,0:21:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But of their own free choice.\NSo that ties in with discipline?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.70,0:21:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I like how.\NWell, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.31,0:21:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This is really what I'm wondering about, is that I have a belief that not eating meat\Nis probably better than eating meat.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.07,0:21:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know this because I'm not a vegetarian, but from a perspective, I can see that as\Na good thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.22,0:21:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAnd I tend to think that...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.85,0:21:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That that is a process that comes, and that the desire for and the tolerance of meat falls\Naway, versus a choice just to become a vegetarian out of a discipline.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.81,0:22:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So at various times, depending on where you are and your level of understanding, it means\Ndifferent things, and therefore your behavior would mean different things.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.90,0:22:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,At one point, it would be adherence.\NWhen I was a Buddhist, strict Buddhist, you know, I kept the butterfly net.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.44,0:22:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I would sit behind the grapes in my office, and between patients, I would take the butterfly\Nnet and catch the flies and put them out the window, because I didn't want to swat one.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.91,0:22:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In those days, I believed in death.\NDeath was a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.20,0:22:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought, if I'm killing the fly, I'm killing life.\NWell, if you think that you can kill life, then you shouldn't be killing life.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.49,0:22:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you realize that life cannot be killed, to the fly, it doesn't make any difference.\NThen you're different.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.57,0:22:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So it all depends on how you're seeing it.\NBecause, see, each level...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.83,0:22:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You're expressing the reality of where you were at spiritually.\NYou're being honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.33,0:22:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,See, while you think of this, you should be doing this.\NWhile you're doing this, you should be doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.11,0:23:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NAnd I guess I still have input from different levels at the same, maybe not the exact same
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.11,0:23:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,moment, but from moment, or a relatively short moment to moment.\NBecause it's not a linear process.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.29,0:23:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a non-linear process.\NAnd so one day, you see this scintillation more than this scintillation.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.11,0:23:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, I was sitting.\NI was sitting at dinner, and they say, what do you want, steak or fish?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.27,0:23:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I always order fish.\NSuddenly, I looked at my meat, and I said, I am meat.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.52,0:23:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have steak, thanks.\NI'm doing the cow a favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.29,0:23:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If I don't eat steak, there's going to be no cows out there.\NMillions of cattle will not have a life.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.29,0:23:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NSo it all depends on how you contextualize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.92,0:23:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I completely understand that.\NYou can serve life by eating it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.70,0:23:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.53,0:24:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo, as I said before, the Rig Veda says that each level of life is sacrificial to that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.78,0:24:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,above it.\NSo, you reward the animal by allowing, by when you eat the animal, you're allowing it
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.03,0:24:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to evolve to a higher level of consciousness by uniting with you and your blessedness.\NAnd in so doing, you bless the animal, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.01,0:24:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it depends on how you wish you envision it.\NI can give you half a dozen of the ways, but that's enough for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.40,0:24:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NI understand that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.03,0:24:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing I'm wondering now, then, because I do...\NNo, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.77,0:24:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NI do understand that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.00,0:24:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd I'm going to walk away with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.27,0:24:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead.\NAnd that is the should.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.74,0:24:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a should that's coming out of ego or judgment or something that I'm still working\Nwith.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.14,0:24:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The should that eating meat is not a good thing.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.57,0:24:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, don't eat it while it's a good thing.\NNot a good thing, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.77,0:24:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NI got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.51,0:25:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThat's one of the things.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.81,0:25:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Money, sex, eating meat.\NThose are the big ones that hit all spiritual students.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.50,0:25:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Money, sex, work, eating meat.\NThose are the traditional.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.50,0:25:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.66,0:25:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a question on the chart that you put up earlier, and this probably comes straight\Nfrom my mammalian ego, but could you account for the difference in calibration between
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.48,0:25:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the...\NChimpanzees as a species, which you say calibrated around 400 and...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.24,0:25:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't say it's a species they calibrated 400.\NPerhaps I misunderstood.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.93,0:25:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I said cocoa reached 400.\NCocoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.11,0:25:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Cocoa is a gorilla.\NLet's take dairy cattle then.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.51,0:25:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember what...\NDo you remember what...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.74,0:25:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Dairy cattle, yeah.\NWas that about...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.16,0:25:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In the 200s.\N250 or so, if I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.48,0:25:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NBut still...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.75,0:25:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Herbivores.\NAnd mankind as a species calibrates now at 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.44,0:26:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So what is the problem?\NFox News instead of ABC, that's my advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.26,0:26:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No, because...\NNo, the problem is that you're trying to understand many things with the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.44,0:26:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The intellect is not the right tool.\NObservation and intuition would be a better way, because then the significance of it dawns
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.14,0:26:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,on you as you're driving along, not even thinking about it, you suddenly see it.\NThe intellect is not the right tool to understand many things about consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.33,0:26:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.82,0:26:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.25,0:26:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.28,0:26:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.39,0:26:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.43,0:26:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.49,0:26:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.54,0:26:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.78,0:26:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.84,0:26:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.13,0:26:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.76,0:26:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.23,0:26:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.78,0:26:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.10,0:26:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.21,0:26:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.39,0:26:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.56,0:26:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.80,0:26:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.71,0:26:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I said.\NI said that's what the...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.65,0:27:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that isn't what I said.\NWhat did I say?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.58,0:27:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I said the Rig Vida states, Krishna states, that each level sacrifices itself to the evolution\Nof life by serving the next level.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.58,0:27:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I said that's what the Rig Vida says.\NSo do these levels...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.42,0:27:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I said the Rig Vida says.\NOkay, the Rig Veda said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.57,0:27:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think these levels correspond to the calibrated levels of consciousness or of life?\NThat what?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.32,0:27:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Do the levels referred to in the Rig Veda\Ncorrespond to the calibrated levels of the species that you had on the chart earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.15,0:27:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I would imagine, yeah.\NGod created the animals and he created the humans and he created the fishes and the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.55,0:27:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Back to my original question about humanity calibrating at 207.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.33,0:28:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And a dairy cow calibrating at 245, which is the lower level.\NOh, some humanity calibrates lower than cattle?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.07,0:28:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, of course they do.\NI got the statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.05,0:28:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever been in a Nazi torture camp?\NNo, I haven't.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.77,0:28:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you won't have any question about it.\NWhole civilizations calibrate at 60 and 70.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.82,0:28:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize there's whole civilizations where you would be executed right now.\NOr even having challenged me with a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.35,0:28:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand that?\NNow you're a brave man.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.22,0:28:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I do.\NWell, he's been brave.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.96,0:29:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But I have the potentiality of reaching a level in the...\NI understand what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.96,0:29:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The content of your question is not the problem.\NThe problem is using the wrong tool to address it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.16,0:29:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,To think that these things are going to fall within explicable logic or reason.\NThey don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.79,0:29:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,They just are.\NThey are what they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.90,0:29:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The inference of it only sort of dawns on you, but it does it in a sort of a non-logical way.\NWhy is it that a donkey calibrates higher than a lot of people on the world...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.13,0:29:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in the planet?\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.47,0:29:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,A donkey's harmless, see?\NYou're safer with a donkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.02,0:29:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You're safer with Coco, the gorilla.\NI can take you to neighborhoods in New York City that are far less safe than being in a cage with Coco.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.22,0:29:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And she's the only gorilla.\NThe dog I met at lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.09,0:29:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You're safe to be with.\NLoving, friendly, trusting.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.90,0:30:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Good sense of humor.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.77,0:30:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.21,0:30:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I said, I'm just...\NI'm just to thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.00,0:30:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That guy's a pal.\NHe comes up in public and gives you a hard time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.51,0:30:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, who...\NIt's a good friend, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.11,0:30:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody can come up and just be friendly and I'll get out.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.61,0:30:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Easy going.\NEasy going.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.83,0:30:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Easy going.\NEasy going.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.18,0:30:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I think.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.58,0:30:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We're trained to rely on the intellect to solve our problems.\NAnd it's hard to get that the intellect will only take you so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.59,0:31:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Many years ago, first reading about Buddhism and Zen and all, in the great dismay, I discovered\Nthat trying harder won't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.98,0:31:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Studying harder, reading more books and trying harder wasn't the answer.\NI can remember the feeling of defeat because the intellect is what I spent all these years
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.72,0:31:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,perfecting.\Nand now I'm told
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.67,0:31:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,they won't do me any good\NI had a follow up question
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.43,0:31:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to the free will question\NI think you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.32,0:31:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,explained that all things happen\Nspontaneously according
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.17,0:31:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to its karmic propensity\Nso do we choose at the level
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.49,0:31:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of form that\Nyou can pick up that pen
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.13,0:31:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,or is it a more abstract level\Nthat you choose truth or illusion
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.47,0:31:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,not in the\Nphysical world
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.21,0:31:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,for potentiality become actuality\Nyeah
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.03,0:31:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,in a generic way it depends on\Nintention
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.95,0:32:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,in a generic way\Nin the ultimate generic
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.94,0:32:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,way it's\Nthe expression of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.71,0:32:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the nature of divinity itself\Nthe energy of divinity is such
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.97,0:32:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that anything you put in\Nits field
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.79,0:32:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,its potentiality now is\Nrealizable
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.51,0:32:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,as an actuality\Njust like magnetism
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.59,0:32:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,on an iron filing\Nit's not personal
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.00,0:32:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,but the quality of the field\Nis for that
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.67,0:32:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,which has potential\Nto mature
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.02,0:32:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to mature\Nso is it my free will
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.20,0:32:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to walk up here\Nor was my free will
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.38,0:32:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,at a different level\Ndid this just arise spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.50,0:32:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that you're here means that that was\Na potentiality that was realized
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.25,0:32:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,before you were here and that's why you're here now\Nit's not possible as an actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.72,0:32:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but only your intention made it happen\Nso my choice is my intention as well
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.16,0:32:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,right\Nso it's all intention
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.31,0:33:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,it's intention not the action\Nthe action is just
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.07,0:33:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,appearance of\Nit's the appearance of creation
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.08,0:33:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,as it unfolds to the witnessing\Nof observation which is its
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.08,0:33:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,expression and physicality\Nthe senses you know what I'm saying
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.10,0:33:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,without the senses nobody would know\Nyou're here so that is on
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.40,0:33:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,a means of\Nsignaling information form is nothing but
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.75,0:33:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,information\Nform is information
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.90,0:33:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the story you tell where\Nyou
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.14,0:33:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,speared the man in the groin and you could have given him a merciful death\Nwas that simply his karma to die on the battlefield
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.50,0:33:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know about his karma I never asked about it\NI had enough karma of my own to worry about it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.48,0:33:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,well we challenged him to die on the battlefield\Nso the warrior is...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.90,0:33:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,oh my gosh\Nthe warrior in the warrior
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.66,0:33:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,they're behind the псie\Nthey really challenged each other y'know
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.85,0:34:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,these are archetypal levels of\Nthe evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.85,0:34:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,since it your collective unconsciousness\Nthe warrior is one of the great ones
